  "prompt": "What are the penalties for money laundering under federal law?",
  "response": "Under federal law, money laundering can result in significant criminal penalties, including:\n\n1. Criminal Penalties:\n- Potential prison sentences of up to 20 years\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Potential forfeiture of assets involved in the transaction\n\n2. Specific Statutory Provisions:\n- 18 U.S. Code \u00a7 1956 covers money laundering criminal offenses\n- Penalties vary based on specific circumstances of the crime\n\n3. Additional Potential Consequences:\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Potential civil penalties\n- Asset seizure\n\nThe exact penalties depend on factors like:\n- Transaction amount\n- Intent\n- Specific type of money laundering\n- Criminal history\n- Whether proceeds involved illegal activities\n\nFor precise details about a specific situation, I recommend consulting a qualified legal professional who can provide authoritative guidance based on the specific circumstances.",
